==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang}} {{term|dom|dōm|[[judgement]]|lang=ang}}, cognate with Old Norse "dómr", Swedish, Danish, and Norwegian "dom"

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/duːm/}}, {{SAMPA|/du:m/}}
* {{audio|en-us-doom.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|uːm}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# [[death|Death]]; an adverse or terrible [[fate]], [[end]].
#: ''They met an untimely '''doom''' when the mine shaft caved in.''
# A [[judgment]] or [[decision]], especially one that has negative consequences.
# {{rfex}} An impending severe problem or danger that seems inevitable.
# {{rfv-sense|can "doom" be a feeling?}} A feeling of [[danger]], impending danger, darkness or despair.
# {{context|sometimes capitalized}} The [[Last Judgment]]; ''or'', an artistic representation of it.

